[3] Chile: alert
Date: Fri 24 Jun 2022 20:50
Source: La Nación [in Spanish trans. Mod.TY, abridged, edited]
https://www.lanacion.com.ar/el-mundo/viruela-del-mono-contabilizan-seis-casos-en-chile-y-declaran-la-alerta-sanitaria-nid24062022/


The Chile government declared a health alert due to the advance of monkeypox in the country. Currently, 6 people have been infected with the disease according to Soy Chile (https://www.soychile.cl/Santiago/Sociedad/2022/06/24/763593/alerta-sanitaria-viruela-del-mono.html).

The national Minister of Health, María Begoña Yarza, issued the announcement together with the international advisor of the Pan American Health Organization, Mario Cruz.

In Chile, the declaration of a health alert implies the injection of more resources for supplies, health residences, specialized personnel, and other types of tools that are needed depending on the contingency.

In any case, the authorities called for calm, a measure with which the specialists who participated in the official announcement agree.

