[5] Brazil
Date: Sat 25 Jun 2022
Source: El Imparcial [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
https://www.elimparcial.com/mundo/Brasil-reporta-sus-primeros-casos-de-viruela-del-mono-en-pacientes-que-no-viajaron-20220625-0091.html


Brazil confirmed this past Thursday [22 Jun 2022] the 1st locally acquired cases (in patients who did not travel recently) of monkeypox, in 3 people living in the city of Sao Paulo.

With the new report, the South American giant adds 14 cases in total and ranks as the nation with the most confirmed infections of the disease in Latin America.

According to the Ministry of Health, the locally acquired cases correspond to 3 men between 24 and 37 years of age "with no history of travel to countries with confirmed cases."

The remaining 11 cases were diagnosed in people who recently visited Spain, Portugal, and England, countries where the disease is on the rise.

Most of the diagnoses have been registered in the state of Sao Paulo, with 10 cases, all in its homonymous capital. The other 4 were reported in the states of Rio de Janeiro and Rio Grande do Sul, with 2 patients each.

According to the Health agency, all cases, all diagnosed patients, including those under suspicion, are isolated and under the supervision of health surveillance teams.

Cases have multiplied in the country in just 2 weeks, after health authorities reported the 1st case in Brazil on 8 Jun 2022.

